The paper proposes a new OS abstraction and structure to address challenges posed by server-side computing, many-core scale, and workload diversity. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses resource discovery, monitoring, and provisioning, which are key aspects of distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.Distributed). The paper also mentions state sharing and confinement, which are relevant to security (cs.SY) and architecture (cs.AR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.OS, cs.DC, and cs.Distributed, followed by cs.SY and cs.AR.
